casebody.data:
MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

95-355. Nos. C-940159, C-940160 and C-940161. Cincinnati v. Durham. Hamilton County,

Appellant has filed an untimely appeal of the court of appeals’ decision entered on December 30,1994. In that appellant has failed to perfect an appeal pursuant to S.Ct-Prac.R. II(2)(A)(1),

IT IS ORDERED by the court, sua sponte, that this case be, and hereby is, dismissed for lack of jurisdiction.
